  "texts": [
    "To prevent improper usage of AI code generation tools, one recent study developed a system to generate textual responses to student requests that are similar to what a human tutor would deliver [37].",
    "However, some students found it difficult to use because they had to type their input and did not always know what to ask.",
    "Furthermore, the long and plain textual materials discouraged active learning unless students used self-explanation while reading the text [11].",
    "In addition, the generated output could be factually incorrect due to the limitations of LLMs.",
    "Recent generative AI models perform well in understanding and generating code outputs, which forms a basis for scalable personalization in programming learning scenarios [48]."
  ],
